<h2>Top Emotions for Ad Copy Domination #2 ‚Äì AFFIRMATION</h2>
<p>Going back to my process again. The client I wrote this next set of ads for is a plus-size fashion retailer, so the target market is plus-size women. The persona I wanted to take on here was the feel-good friend.</p>
<p>Here was the ad that was originally running in the account, prior to testing. It was pretty generic. This ad always had a pretty good click-through rate, so we never really played around with it too much.</p>
<div class="embedded-entity align-center" data-embed-button="images" data-entity-embed-display="view_mode:media.simple_image" data-entity-type="media" data-entity-uuid="f459fd98-e691-4c1c-a458-24da7051447f" data-langcode="en">
<article>
<div><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/emotional-ads-affirmation-ad.png" alt="Emotional ads affirmation" width="411" height="154" /></div>
</article>
</div>
<p>I decided to throw in two ads to run simultaneously with the original ad. One was an ad that focused on flattering the user.</p>
<div class="embedded-entity align-center" data-embed-button="images" data-entity-embed-display="view_mode:media.simple_image" data-entity-type="media" data-entity-uuid="e5395d7f-8634-4248-9a46-f29268df87a5" data-langcode="en">
<article>
<div><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/emotional-ads-affirmation-ad-2.png" alt="Emotional ad affirmation " width="443" height="128" /></div>
</article>
</div>
<p>I was biased towards this ad, and wanted it to do well, but it actually didn‚Äôt do so great, because it was a bit off-topic from the core product ‚Äì clothing. Here was the other ad I put into the rotation:</p>
<div class="embedded-entity align-center" data-embed-button="images" data-entity-embed-display="view_mode:media.simple_image" data-entity-type="media" data-entity-uuid="a0e37625-6421-48c7-b450-5212e448a0af" data-langcode="en">
